<HEAD>Tiger Attacks Handler At Sydney Zoo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A tiger mauled a handler at <LOCATION> Sydney </LOCATION>'s Taronga Park Zoo on Saturday, leaving her in critical condition <PERSON> Victoria </PERSON> <PERSON> Scrivener </PERSON>, 33, was rushed to the hospital with severe injuries to her head and upper body after being attacked when she apparently tried to separate the female <LOCATION> Sumatran </LOCATION> tiger from her cubs. A spokesman for the zoo, who declined to be identified, said the zoo was investigating the incident. Dr. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON>, acting medical superintendent for the <LOCATION> Royal </LOCATION> <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Shore </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION>, said Ms. <PERSON> Scrivener </PERSON> was in critical condition Saturday night. A colleague who entered the tiger cage with her was not hurt, according to the zoo spokesman. He refused to comment further and said the findings of the inquiry would not be available for some time.
</TEXT>
