Workers Commissions appeared at a large, peaceful demonstration in central <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION> and rejected the meeting offered by <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON> if he insists the head of the nation's key business organization attend. At least 40,000 people attended the rally. Despite an economic growth rate of 5 percent annually that puts it at the top of Western European economies, 18.7 percent of the people are unemployed, <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s highest rate. Union leaders and members have argued the time has come to share more of the spoils of economic boom with workers and the poor.
