<DATELINE>VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Students cowered and cried `` Jesus save us! God save us!'' as a 16-year-old boy opened fire in their Bible class after he killed one teacher and wounded another, police said. The boy fired two shots in the classroom but did not hit anyone before his MAC-10 commando-style machine pistol jammed and he was subdued by a teacher and students at the <ORGANIZATION> Atlantic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>, authorities said. `` Once you see what went on in there, it's a miracle that we did n't have more people killed,'' Police Chief <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wall </PERSON> said Friday. Police spokesman <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> <PERSON> Thurston </PERSON> said the 10th-grader was charged with first-degree murder, malicious assault, four counts of attempted murder, six counts of using a gun to commit a crime and three counts of discharging a firearm in an occupied building. He was in custody today.
